DIARRHEA - BANGLADESH: (RAJSHAHI) REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
*********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 27 Dec 2021
Source: Dhaka Tribune [abridged, edited]
https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/nation/2021/12/27/chapainawabganj-hospital-overwhelmed-with-diarrhoea-patients


Chapainawabganj, a north western border district, is seeing an outbreak of diarrhea as at least 50-60 children have been reportedly hospitalized every day in the last 10-15 days. "Comprising the ward's sofas and beds, we can accommodate 24 patients. But as the number is 5 to 6 times higher, many are staying on floor," said senior staff nurse Nasrin Khatun.

"It's hard to even have a space in the veranda outside the diarrhea ward for my 2 year old granddaughter," said a woman from Maharajpur village, who admitted her granddaughter on Monday [27 Dec 2021].

Dr Mahfuzur Rayhan, junior consultant (children) of Chapainawabganj district hospital, said that in the last 8-10 days, the numbers of diarrhoea patients have increased, as winter is the season of spreading rotavirus. He assured there is nothing to fear as proper treatment ensures full recovery.

Dr Md Mominul Haque, supervisor of the hospital, said: "There is no shortage of saline, medicines, and we are fully prepared to treat the children being admitted at the hospital." He said the hospital authority has covered the corridor area with clothes to save the children and their parents from the cold.

--
communicated by:
ProMED

[The etiology or etiologies of the increase in diarrheal illness in this area of Bangladesh is not clear. ProMED would be grateful for further information if a definitive diagnosis is made. - Mod.LL

